main event: The UFO report documents sightings and observations in Seattle, Washington on July 6, 1956. The report mentions multiple sightings of unidentified objects, some with photographs and others without, as well as radar observations.
interesting points: The report includes sightings of two objects leaving vapor trails and a single silver-colored object observed directly overhead, which later exploded.
Aircraft were in the area at the time of the sightings, and one object appeared to be a star initially but then performed unusual actions.
Observations mention radar detections of an object with high altitude and water trail, circling, and then fading from sight.
Some observations reported prior sightings of shooting stars before the unidentified object sightings.
The report contains little data to base an evaluation, and the conclusion suggests possibilities of the objects being balloons, aircraft, or astronomical phenomena.
witnesses: 2 subjects, civilian source, and ground radar station
